Perpetual Energy Shares Plunge 31% After Dividend is Suspended

-- B y   M a t t   W a l c o f f
-- 
2011-10-20T14:54:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/perpetual-energy-shares-plunge-31-after-dividend-is-suspended.html
Perpetual Energy Inc. (PMT) , which
produces natural gas in  Canada , plunged 31 percent in Toronto
Stock Exchange trading, the most since 2003, to C$1.59 after
suspending its dividend. The company cited weakness in natural
gas prices, which sank 26 percent from June 8 to yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matt Walcoff in Toronto at 
